This is a very interesting look at Australia from both sides of the 
Multicultural debate and asylum seeker controversy.

I was once married for four + years  to a lovely gal from Australia named
Elizabeth whose parents had French roots and I grew especially fond of 
Australia even more so for this reason along with such factors as having 
had an extremely kindly and supremely intelligent and humanly beautiful
(I found) Australian Headmaster at the British run Boarding School I 
had attended briefly in my younger days on the African continent. 

I initially viewed this video on Kanopy.com which provides on-line
viewing for those with a local library card number. (Whichever cities
they may now be including in this at this point). I got this video 
copy in 1080p for you folks here - enjoy!


Michael Rizzo Chessman
